# Describe the problem
  As a user, so that I can improve my grammar, I want to verify that a text
  starts with a capital letter and ends with a suitable punctuation mark. 

# Design the method signature
check_grammar(text)

Returns true if text starts with a capital letter and ends in the right punctuation. 
Otheriwse, returns false.

# Create examples to test
check_grammar("I can code.") => "Your grammar is correct"
check_grammar("I can code?") => "Your grammar is correct"
check_grammar("i can code?") => "Your grammar is incorrect"
check_grammar("I can code") => "Your grammar is incorrect"
check_grammar("i can code") => "Your grammar is incorrect"